(1) Subject to sections eight, nine, ten and eleven the estate of an intestate shall be distributed as follows: (a) twenty per cent of the estate shall devolve upon the surviving spouse; except that where more than one widow survives the intestate , twenty per cent of the estate shall be distributed among them proportional to the duration of their respective marriages to the deceased, and other factors such as the widow's contribution to the deceased's property may be taken into account when justice so requires; (b) fifty per cent of the estate shall devolve upon the children in such proportions as are commensurate with a child 's age or educational needs or both; (c) twenty per cent of the estate shall devolve upon the parents of the deceased; (d) ten per cent of the estate shall devolve upon the dependants, in equal shares: Provided that a priority dependant whose portion of the estate under this section is unreasonably small having regard to his degree of dependence on the deceased shall have the right to apply to a court for adjustment to be made to the portions inherited and in that case, Part III of the Wills and Administration of Testate Estates Act shall apply, with the necessary changes, to the application. [ Cap. 60 ]
