(1) The duties and powers of an administrator shall be— (a) to pay the debts and funeral expenses of the deceased and pay estate duty if estate duty is payable; (b) to effect distribution of the estate in accordance with the rights of the persons interested in the estate under this Act; (c) when required to do so by the court, either on the application of an interested party or on its own motion— (i) to produce on oath in court the full inventory of the estate of the deceased; and (ii) to render to the court an account of the administration of the estate .
