(1) Letters of administration may be revoked or annulled for any of the following reasons— (a) that the proceedings to obtain them were defective in substance; (b) that the grant was obtained fraudulently; (c) that the grant was obtained by means of an untrue statement of a fact essential in point of law to justify the grant, though that statement was made in ignorance or inadvertently; (d) that the grant has become of no use and inoperative; (e) that the person to whom the grant was made has, without reasonable cause failed, to furnish an account of his administration after having been lawfully called upon to do so, or has prepared an account which is untrue in a material particular.
